This article discusses the importance of remembering the Holocaust on International Holocaust Remembrance Day. It emphasizes the horrific nature of the Holocaust, in which six million Jews were systematically slaughtered, along with other groups targeted by the Nazis. The article calls the Holocaust a crime against humanity and against God. It stresses the need to remember and honor the victims and survivors of the Holocaust, and to prevent such suffering from happening again. The phrase "Never Again" is mentioned, highlighting the commitment to ensuring that such atrocities are not repeated. The article also acknowledges the individuals who have dedicated their lives to the preservation and security of the Jewish people and the betterment of humanity.